Citations
Date: 22/7/1908
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 32
Edition:
Quote: "The hotel, which is situated about three miles from the top of the pass, has for the past week been crowded with travellers who have got so far on their journey into the Mackenzie Country, but at present can go no further: snow-rakers going up in hot haste to some of the back stations, station-owners who have been down-country for the winter anxious to get through and learn the fate of their stock - all waiting for the first opportunity to make a dash over the pass ..."
