Author:
Vol / Page: 24
Edition:
Quote: The shepherds, in many instances, go prodding about in the snowdrifts with long poles, after the manner of the kauri gum digger using his spear, and if the pole did not strike the sheep, or the snowraker fall through on top of it, he might very easily walk within a foot of it and be unaware of its presence.
